#2472
On a misty path~
You travel along a stoney, gray path beneith you, wide enough to fit three
humans abreast. You glance around, starting at the empty void which lies
on either side of the stone path. A few feet into the blackness, a strange
crimson and gray mist swirls, obscuring your vision. Even though there are
no visible light sources, the path is well lit.
An eerie tower rises up from the mist to the west. Its surface is
entirely made of black, glass-like stone which reflects an otherwordly
rainbow of scintillating colors. No windows can be been seen to mar the
walls of this spire. A narrow walkway winds its way through the mists
to a massive vallenwood door.
~
100 552 0 7
0 0 0 0
0 0 0
