#2704
The fiery entryway~
The floor of this chamber is flooded with molten lava.  Bubbles of
hot air burst and send small dropplets of searing debris flying.
Threatening gysers of flame errupt from the floor and streak high into
the shadow-filled regions of the upper tower.  Narrow pathways twist and
bend through the lake of lava, providing access to a series of floating
marble slabs, serving as a staircase leading up.
